  "title": "Matrix Modeling - steady state",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div class=\"qti-layout-row\"> <div class=\"qti-layout-col12\"> <div class=\"prompt\"> <p class=\"dap_body\">Objects in a system can be in two possible states: state&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\"><mn>1</mn></math></span>&nbsp;and state&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\"><mn>2</mn></math></span>. The vector&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"vector v equals a 2 by 1 vector where row 1 is 0.3 and row 2 is 0.7\"><math alttext=\"vector v equals a 2 by 1 vector where row 1 is 0.3 and row 2 is 0.7\"><mover><mi>v</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0.3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0.7</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></span>&nbsp;gives the&nbsp;probability that an object is in each state. If matrix&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\"><mi>A</mi></math></span>&nbsp;is the transition matrix for these states and&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"A times vector v equals vector v\"><math alttext=\"A times vector v equals vector v\"><mi>A</mi><mover><mi>v</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mover><mi>v</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></math></span>, which of the following can be concluded?</p> </div> </div> </div>\n",
    "answer": "D-43218",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"dap_body\">Because the vector is not&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"a 2 by 1 vector where row 1 is 0.5 and row 2 is 0.5\"><math alttext=\"a 2 by 1 vector where row 1 is 0.5 and row 2 is 0.5\"><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0.5</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0.5</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></span>, the system will not reach a steady state.</p>",
        "value": "A-43215"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"dap_body\">Because the vector is not&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"a 2 by 1 vector where row 1 is 0.5 and row 2 is 0.5\"><math alttext=\"a 2 by 1 vector where row 1 is 0.5 and row 2 is 0.5\"><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0.5</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0.5</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></span>, there must be more steps to find the steady state.</p>",
        "value": "B-43216"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"dap_body\">Because the vector remains unchanged, the transition matrix must be the identity matrix.</p>",
        "value": "C-43217"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"dap_body\">Because the vector remains unchanged, in the long run, the system has about&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"30 percent sign\"><math alttext=\"30 percent sign\"><mn>30</mn><mo>%</mo></math></span>&nbsp;in one state and&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"70 percent sign\"><math alttext=\"70 percent sign\"><mn>70</mn><mo>%</mo></math></span>&nbsp;in the other state.</p>",
        "value": "D-43218"
      }
